        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 4:47PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 447 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from Talking Rock to Forney, and moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Heavy rain and slow to stationary storms may cause
temporary street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Rome, Cartersville, Calhoun, Cedartown, Jasper, Adairsville,
Euharlee, Aragon, Cave Spring, White, Waleska, Kingston, Plainville,
Taylorsville, Talking Rock, Shannon, Cassville, Fairmount, Ranger,
and Pinson.
</description>
        <instruction>Motorists should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of
control due to hydroplaning.</instruction>
